    {
      "chunk_id": 223,
      "page": 2,
      "section": "Page 2",
      "text": "This  LOI  is  independent  of  and  does  not  modify  LPU’s  academic  regulations. Sincerely,    Best  Regards   \n Vikas  Gupta   Chairman  &  Managing  Director,  Futurense  Technologies  Private  Limited  \nANNEXURE  -  I  :  PLACEMENT  –  ELIGIBILITY,  READINESS  &  CTC  BANDS   \nA. Eligibility  &  Readiness  Criteria   a. Academics :  Minimum  60%  aggregate  in  Class  X  &  XII;  ≥ 60%  aggregate  in    graduation;  no  active  backlogs  at  the  time  of  placement  drives. b. Attendance :  ≥ 85%  average  attendance  across  semesters  and  mandatory    participation  in  Futurense-led  training,  assessments,  mock  interviews,  and    projects. c.  Assessments :  Satisfactory  performance  in  Futurense  Placement  Exams  (aptitude,    communication,  DSA,  technical  stack)  and  mock  interviews  as  per  rubric. d.  Conduct  &  Integrity :  Adherence  to  academic  integrity  and  assessment  protocols    (including  proctoring). Attempts  outside  approved  protocols  are  invalid. e.  Projects/Capstone/Internships :  Completion  with  required  reviews  and  sign-offs. f.  Behavioral  Conduct :  Good  character  and  no  criminal  records. Professionalism    should  be  maintained  throughout  the  program  and  internships. g.  Completion  Certificate :  Completion  of  a  degree  with  Lovely  Professional"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": 224,
      "page": 3,
      "section": "Page 3",
      "text": "University  is  mandatory   B. Placement  Facilitation  Inclusions   a. Structured  placement  training,  resume/LinkedIn  clinic,  and  interview  simulations. b.  Shortlisting  support  and  interview  coordination  with  partner  employers. c.  Performance  Improvement  Plan  and  re-attempts  if  readiness  gates  aren’t  met. C.  Offer  Refusals  &  Mobility   a. Up  to  one  (1)  refusals  ofsuitable  offers  are  permitted  without  penalty;  thereafter,    assistance  may  pause  for  up  to  60  days. b. Roles  may  require  pan-India  mobility,  hybrid/onsite  work,  or  rotational  shifts,  as    per  employer  policy. D.  CTC  Bands  (Indicative;  employer  decides  final  CTC)   a. Composite  Performance  —  Expected  CTC  (Indicative)   i.  CGPA  ≥  6.0  AND  ≥  60%  in  Futurense  Projects  AND  Placement  Exams  cleared   —  INR  6  LPA   ii. CGPA  ≥  7.0  AND  ≥  70%  in  Projects  AND  good  interview  rubric  —  INR  7  –  9    LPA   iii. CGPA  ≥  8.0  AND  ≥  80%  in  Projects  AND  strong  internship  evaluations  AND   interview  rubric  ( ≥ A-)  —  INR  10  –  12  LPA   iv. CGPA  ≥  9.0  AND  ≥  90%  in  Projects  AND  top-decile  interview  rubric  AND   leadership  in  capstone  —  INR  12  LPA  &  above   b. Upgrade  rule:  Exceeding  thresholds  in  two  or  more  dimensions  may  qualify  you    for  consideration  in  the  next  higher  band,  subject  to  employer  decision."
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": 225,
      "page": 3,
      "section": "Page 3",
      "text": "Note :  This  Annexure  is  indicative  and  may  be  reasonably  updated  to  reflect  market  dynamics   while  preserving  fairness. ANNEXURE  -  II  :  INTERNSHIP  STIPEND  POLICY  (AIDE  SPECIALIZATION)   \nA.  Stipend  Table   a. First  Internship  —  Year-2  —  3  months  —  Maximum  Overall  Stipend  (Gross):  INR    15,000   b. Second  Internship  —  Year-3  —  3  months  —  Maximum  Overall  Stipend  (Gross):  INR    20,000   c.  Third  Internship  —  Year-4  —  6  months  —  Maximum  Overall  Stipend  (Gross):  INR    1,10,000   B.  Disbursement  mechanics  (indicative,  subject  to  Clause  D  below):   a. First  Internship:  Up  to  INR  12,000  base  +  up  to  INR  3,000  performance  bonus"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": 226,
      "page": 4,
      "section": "Page 4",
      "text": "(monthly  reviews). b. Second  Internship:  Up  to  INR  12,000  base  +  up  to  INR  8,000  performance  bonus    (monthly  reviews). c.  Third  Internship:  Up  to  INR  60,000  base  +  up  to  INR  50,000  performance  bonus    (reviewed  across  tenure). C.  Bonus  Eligibility  (per  month/tenure,  as  applicable)   a. Attendance:  ≥ 90%  (working  hours,  check-ins,  deliverables). b. Performance:  ≥ 85%  on  rubric  (quality,  velocity,  reliability,  collaboration). c.  Compliance:  Security,  confidentiality,  reporting  cadence. D.  Payment  Terms   a. Complete  Amount  disbursement;  pro-rata  for  partial  months;  TDS  and  statutory    deductions  as  per  law. b. Bonuses  are  non-guaranteed  and  contingent  on  meeting  the  rubric  and    attendance  thresholds. E.  Discretion  &  Continuity   a.  Stipend/bonus  figures  are  indicative  and  may  be  updated  by  Futurense  based  on    market  and  program  realities. b.  Internship  continuity  across  Year  -  2/3/4  is  strongly  expected;  withdrawal  or  non   performance  may  impact  future  internship/bonus  eligibility. *This  policy  does  not  create  an  employment  relationship. Internship  opportunities,  project    allocation,  and  stipend  eligibility  remain  at  the  sole  discretion  of  Futurense,  guided  by    transparent  rubrics. *  \nANNEXURE  -  III  :  INTERNSHIP  RULES,  CONDUCT  &  GENERAL  TERMS   \n1."
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": 227,
      "page": 4,
      "section": "Page 4",
      "text": "Status :  You  are  an  intern/trainee,  not  an  employee  of  Futurense;  no  employment  benefits    accrue  from  this  LOI. 2. Work  Mode :  On-campus  (LPU)/Futurense  office/remote,  as  assigned. 3. Equipment  &  Security :  BYOD  laptop  meeting  baseline  specs;  maintain  OS  updates,    antivirus,  VPN,  and  follow  data  security  SOPs. 4. Confidentiality  &  IP :  You  shall  sign  NDA. All  internship  deliverables  and  IP  created  on    program  work  belong  to  Futurense  and/or  its  clients. 5. Mentorship :  A  mentor  guides  scope  and  reviews;  they  do  not  author  the  solution. Self   learning  is  expected. 6. Performance  &  Deadlines :  Use  agreed  sprint  cadences. On  risk  of  slippage,  notify  mentor    early;  PIP  may  be  applied. 7. Non-compliance/Misconduct :  Plagiarism,  unauthorized  data  use,  or  protocol  breaches"
    },
